CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 2, 1955, pg. 26 reads: " Thousands Thrilled at Courier Home Service Fair...10. Mrs. Lucille Johnson capably handled the Lawry's Company booth, represented by Bill Hop of Los Angeles, Calif. One of the many visitors is sampling Lawry's Spaghetti Sauce...Harris Photos"
TitMainTitle: Lucille Johnson standing behind Lawry's Seasoned Salt booth serving visitors in Syria Mosque for the 1955 Pittsburgh Courier Home Service Fair
